-- Dubai's DFM Drops to Lowest in 4 Months as Abu Dhabi Merger Talks Advance
-- Zahraa Alkhalisi
-- 2010-06-29T07:58:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/dubai-s-dfm-drops-to-lowest-in-4-months-as-abu-dhabi-merger-talks-advance.html

          
          
             Dubai Financial Market PJSC  dropped
to the lowest in almost four months after  Alrroya Aleqtissadiya 
reported that talks to merge the bourse with the Abu Dhabi
Securities Exchange are at an “advanced” stage.  
 The shares retreated  4.6 percent  to 1.45 dirhams, the
lowest level since March 8, as of 11:41 a.m. in Dubai. The stock
has declined 23 percent  this year .  
 Dubai Financial Market, the only Gulf Arab market to sell
shares to the public, has been valued at 9.5 billion dirhams
($2.6 billion),  the newspaper  said. The combined bourses will be
named Emirates Financial Market.  
